# React Patterns

- Functional components only, no class components
- Use `useState` for local state, no external state management
- Extract reusable sub-components (e.g., `ActionIcon`) in the same file
- Event handlers as arrow functions or named functions
- Accessibility: use semantic HTML, proper `aria-` attributes where needed
- RTL support: use logical CSS properties when possible

## Form Handling

```jsx
// Use controlled inputs with single state object
const [formData, setFormData] = useState({ name: "", phone: "" });
const handleChange = (field) => (e) =>
  setFormData((d) => ({ ...d, [field]: e.target.value }));
```

